                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2640: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-18T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 18, 1922—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For Stevens: Your August 15, 2 p.m.</p>
                <p>Legation Peking is being instructed by telegraph to point out to Chinese
                    authorities how prejudicial to China’s interests and her relations with other
                    Powers is the continuance of the situation in the railway zone to which you
                    refer. Similar action was taken with reference to your June 30, 2 p.m. …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
